## Detailed Checklist

Use this full checklist for larger or riskier changes.

### Code Quality
- [ ] `vp check` passes with zero errors and zero warnings
- [ ] `vp check --fix` was run if there were auto-fixable issues
- [ ] No `any` types introduced without an accompanying explanation comment
- [ ] No `@ts-ignore` or `@ts-expect-error` without an explanation comment
- [ ] No `console.log`, `console.debug`, or debugging statements left in
- [ ] No commented-out code blocks
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets, API keys, or credentials

### Tests
- [ ] `vp test` passes with zero failures
- [ ] New features have corresponding tests in the same commit
- [ ] Bug fixes have a corresponding regression test in the same commit
- [ ] No tests were skipped or commented out to make the suite pass

### Database (if this commit touches `src/db/`)
- [ ] All new tables use `generateId()` from `$db/utils/id` for the primary key (not `randomUUIDv7` imported directly from `'bun'`)
- [ ] All new tables have `created_at` and `updated_at` columns
- [ ] Tables with soft-deletable records have a `deleted_at` column
- [ ] A Drizzle migration has been generated for schema changes (`vp run db:migrate` or `drizzle-kit generate`)
- [ ] The migration file has been reviewed and looks correct
- [ ] TypeBox schemas have been created or updated in `src/db/typebox/` for any modified tables
- [ ] The `@sinclair/typebox` version pin in `package.json` is still correct

### API (if this commit touches `src/api/`)
- [ ] The route is under `/api/v1/`
- [ ] The route has auth middleware applied
- [ ] The route has RBAC permission check applied
- [ ] The route has a TypeBox schema for `body`, `query`, and/or `params` as appropriate
- [ ] The route has a Swagger tag assigned (for OpenAPI documentation)
- [ ] Step 2 business logic validation is implemented for all cross-reference checks
- [ ] Errors use the standard error response shape `{ message, code?, field? }`
- [ ] The audit log is written for any state-changing operation

### UI / SvelteKit (if this commit touches `src/routes/` or `src/lib/components/`)
- [ ] API calls use Eden Treaty, not raw `fetch`
- [ ] Forms use Superforms with a TypeBox schema
- [ ] All form states are handled: idle, loading, success, validation error, server error, network error
- [ ] No inline `style=""` attributes (use Tailwind classes)
- [ ] No `{@html ...}` with unsanitized user content
- [ ] No relative `../` import chains — all imports use path aliases

### Auth and Security
- [ ] No new endpoint is missing auth middleware
- [ ] No new endpoint is missing RBAC permission check
- [ ] No environment variables are read inline with `process.env` or `Bun.env` — use the config module
- [ ] No secrets or API keys in staged files
- [ ] `.env` files are not staged (must be in `.gitignore`)

### Commit Message
- [ ] Message follows Conventional Commits format: `type(scope): description`
- [ ] Type is one of: `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `style`, `ci`, `perf`
- [ ] Description is in imperative mood ("add", "fix", "remove" — not "added", "fixing")
- [ ] Description is specific enough to understand without opening the diff
- [ ] Subject line is 72 characters or fewer
- [ ] No period at the end of the subject line
- [ ] This commit contains only one logical unit of change

